snippet: A 6.2 magnitude earthquake struck the northern coast of Chile on Saturday, the U.S. Geological Survey said, but there were no immediate reports of damage or casualties....

headline.print_headline: 6.2 Magnitude Earthquake Hits Northern Chile, No Damage Reported
headline.main: 6.2 Magnitude Earthquake Hits Northern Chile, No Damage Reported

lead_paragraph: A 6.2 magnitude earthquake struck the northern coast of Chile on Saturday, the U.S. Geological Survey said, but there were no immediate reports of damage or casualties.
